1
2 (a) As used in this article:
3
4 (iv) "Certificate" means a credential other than
5 a degree as defined in paragraph (vi) of this subsection. A
6 "certificate" is either an associate of applied science
7 degree, or indicates satisfactory completion of training in
8 an academic year program of study offered by a Wyoming
9 community college or satisfactory completion of a program
10 of study offered by a Wyoming community college that
11 results in a license, permit, certificate or other
12 government or industry recognized qualification for working
13 in a trade or occupation in this state, including, but not
14 limited to, drivers of commercial motor vehicles, welders,
15 machine shop operators or other workforce training
16 programs;
17
18 21-16-1303. Hathaway scholarship program; eligibility
19 requirements.
20
21 (b) Under the Hathaway scholarship program, subject
22 to availability of funds as determined by the legislature,
23 the state shall provide a scholarship pursuant to W.S.
